The paper deals with subspace embeddings, which are a fundamental tool in numerical linear algebra and have applications in various areas such as compressed sensing, machine learning, and data analysis. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) the most likely categories. The paper also involves the use of exponential random variables, which are a common tool in information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents protocols for distributed $\ell_p$-regression, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.SI).
